Optical image stabilization is one of [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/camcorder-reviewer/Camcorder_Reviewer-Panasonic_VDR-D230_Review.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img src="http://www.camcorderreviewer.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/02/panasonic-vdr-d230-review.jpg" alt="Panasonic VDR-D230 Review" align="left" />The <em>Panasonic VDR-D230</em> DVD Palmcorder Camcorder is a lightweight, compact recording device that delivers outstanding image quality. The system is well equipped with many great features that are easily accessible and simple to use. The unit offers a user-friendly appeal and advanced features all wrapped up in one petite device.</p>
<p>Optical image stabilization is one of the most appealing features offered by the Panasonic VDR-D230 camcorder. The unit promises smooth footage and blur-free images even when recording takes place in very bumpy conditions. The unit adjusts itself according to outside movements.</p>
<p>Camera shake is virtually a thing of the past with the Palmcorder’s optical image stabilization. This is one of many great features that are built into the unit to enhance picture quality. Users can expect smooth results whether they are recording on a still surface or whether they are capturing footage on a moving boat.</p>
<p>The system is also endowed with a built-in SD slot that provides room for a SD Memory Card that is capable of storing footage. Users can rest assured that the memory card offers ample space for extra video and still shots. The memory card can be used to transfer the data collected by the camera to a personal computer for sharing.</p>
<p>The Panasonic VDR-D230 also allows users to record footage and still shots right on to an 8cm DVD disc. The camera operator simple pushes a button for recording to start. Once recording is finished, he is easily able to view the results by removing the newly burned DVD and putting it into a compatible DVD player.</p>
<p>The results are certain to please with advanced video capture features built into the unit that are designed for outstanding picture quality and vivid detail. The system is equipped with 32x optical zoom that promises excellent footage and still images even when the subject is brought up close from a distance.</p>
<p>The Panasonic VDR-D230 DVD Palmcorder Camcorder has much more to offer. This unit is certain to produce outstanding results time and time again.</p>
