<p>The 16:9 widescreen flat panel display is one of the most appealing features on the unit. Users can see exactly how the footage will look as they capture the action. The 2.7-inch LCD monitor is ideal for viewing the great results and it serves as a great tool for capturing images with that knowledge that the end result will be the same.</p>
<p>The realistic view offered by the 16:9 widescreen display is emphasized by the generous field of vision and the excellent picture quality. The Clear LCD feature is handy in reducing glare and reflection, allowing for clarity and outstanding visibility. This feature also works well outdoors and in direct sunlight for optimal viewing.</p>
<p>The JVC Mini DVD GR-D750 camcorder offers a dual recording mode that allows users to take still images and video simultaneously. The still image function has the capacity to allow users to take and store images. In addition, the unit comes with supplied software that can be used for editing an organizing the images on a personal computer.</p>
<p>The unit is remarkably easy to use in spite of its advanced features. The system comes equipped with stick control on the LCD. This feature allows users to access many different functions using a four-way one-finger control located right on the LCD door. This makes navigating the system remarkably easy.</p>
<p>This JVC mini DVD camcorder also features 34x optical zoom and when this feature is used with digital zoom, the image can be enlarged up to 800 times without distortion or blurred edges. The system is equipped with NightAlive for superior illumination even in darker areas.</p>
<p>The JVC Mini DVD GR-D750 camcorder is the ideal home video camera for beginners. Seasoned photographers will also appreciate the many amenities offered by this user-friendly device.</p>
